Orbital Teleportation System
This document is for review by the United States Department
of Defense (US DOD) and associated authorized personnel
only. Unauthorized use is prohibited.
Overview:
The Orbital Teleportation System (OTS) is Scabor
Corporation's latest innovation in medium-range
transportation, allowing near-instantaneous transportation
between two locations, provided each location has an OTS
receiver and sender.
Applications:
Though the OTS was originally designed for use by Scabor
Corporation and associated agencies for medium-range
ground-to-orbit transportation, the system can have a wide
range of applications outside of this field, especially in
defense. The system can be adapted to work with only
ground-based receivers and senders, allowing the client to
near-instantaneously transport an individual or individuals.
Range: 0 - 250 miles
A joint project between Scabor Corporation's Exploratory
and Defense teams, the OTS has been extensively tested to
the highest standard of safety.
